<!--
  CLAUDE.md.example — the committed template for your agent's persona.

  HOW TO USE: copy this to CLAUDE.md (which is gitignored), then make it yours.

      cp CLAUDE.md.example CLAUDE.md

  WHY this split: Claude Code automatically loads CLAUDE.md from its working
  directory as system context — so the CLAUDE.md sitting next to agent.py IS your
  agent's persona, loaded every turn with no wiring. Keeping the real one
  gitignored means your agent's identity, voice, and private operating rules never
  land in the (public) repo. Changes are then always one of two things: generic
  engine/tool code (committed) or personality (your uncommitted CLAUDE.md). This
  file, CLAUDE.md.example, is the version a fresh cloner sees.

  Keep secrets OUT of CLAUDE.md too — it may reference notes/brain dirs that ARE
  private, but secrets themselves go in .env (gitignored) and are named here only
  (e.g. "the API key in $SERVICE_TOKEN"). Fill in the TODOs and delete this comment.

  For a complete, worked example, see examples/builder/CLAUDE.md.
-->

